  "title": "Company Driver (Part-Time)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Employment Type:</strong> Part-Time<br /><strong>Work Period:</strong> <strong>19 – 25 January 2026</strong></p><h3><strong>Job Description</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Provide safe, punctual, and professional chauffeuring services for the Chairman.</p></li><li><p>Run errands as directed by the Chairman or Admin Manager.</p></li><li><p>Maintain vehicle cleanliness, hygiene, and overall condition.</p></li><li><p>Perform daily vehicle checks, including petrol and water levels.</p></li><li><p>Arrange and coordinate vehicle inspections, servicing, and road tax renewals.</p></li><li><p>Support ad-hoc duties, including basic administrative tasks when required.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Job Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Possess a valid <strong>Class 3 driving licence</strong> with a clean traffic record.</p></li><li><p>Minimum <strong>5 years of driving experience</strong>, including at least <strong>3 years as a Personal/Company Driver</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Strong safety awareness and excellent driving skills.</p></li><li><p>Proficient in <strong>Mandarin and English</strong>.</p></li><li><p>Punctual with good time management skills.</p></li><li><p>Familiar with Singapore roads and traffic regulations.</p></li><li><p>Willing to work overtime, late hours, weekends, and public holidays when required.</p></li><li><p>High level of integrity and ability to maintain confidentiality.</p></li><li><p>Positive attitude, reliable, and strong work ethic.</p></li><li><p><strong>Immediate availability during the stated period is required.</strong></p></li></ul>",
